:: Agree? {"position":"6225,2950","size":"200,200"}
Scraprat agrees that she should inspect him, he gets on a med bed while in severe pain, and Red draws near. Then extreme pain bursts forth from behind Scraprat's eyes as the alien burrows out of his one eye socket. Comet then almost immediately kicks the alien away and tries to shoot it multiple times with her gun. But the alien manages to escape into the ventilation system.
[[Get acepted in tribe]]


:: Bad End Death {"position":"3100,200","size":"100,100"}
Damn only killed one.


:: Beg for life {"position":"6100,2175","size":"100,200"}
Scraprat begs Comet to spare him, trying to explain that there might be a why to cure him and get rid of the alien entirely.
[[chrisma fail]] 


:: Comet talks him down {"position":"6350,1775","size":"200,200"}
They put their hands up and Comet tries to talk it out with Scraprat, explaining that he could be a threat to everyone. If he cares at all for the lives of people around him, he would realize that dying is the best option.
[[ScrapRat "logs out"]]
[[Struggle]]


:: Dhi check {"position":"6075,3000","size":"100,100"}
Does Scraprat let her inspect him?
[[Agree?]]
[[Disagree?]]


:: Disagree? {"position":"6175,3200","size":"200,200"}
Scraprat refuses to be inspected and the pain finally goes away. Comet understands that the alien would probably not let people get too close. She then asks Red if there are any other options. She then explains that the alien's influence probably strengthens the longer it goes on, since it eats away the brain. But if the host realizes what is happening early enough, they would be able to resist the alien much more, as Scraprat has. So, to ensure that the alien can't simply find a new ignorant host, they should explain the situation when they get back to the rest.
[[The fear is real]]


